I have forever had issues with my time management and productivity. The Pomodoro technique has been around since the late 80s or early 90s, I just discovered it through a therapist friend of mine who suggested it. It has been absolutely incredible for me as far as time management, increase productivity, not only allowing me to start projects but work strategically to finish them. I had been using the timer on my phone, but this app with its integrated list, has been wonderful and indispensable!

I find too little value in paying for the app than using the free version. How about providing the ability to track pomodoros with in a task/activity. Rite now all my pomodoros with in a day are summed up. For ex: If I want to complete enough pomodoros to finish my 8hrs work day but decides to take a break to read something for an hour in between, now since all of the pomodoros are summed up, even casual reading shows I've actually worked. This is the need of the hour in work from home set up.
